@node Documentation " Documentation "

 -The FileShowData is a datafile which contains information about
  files (from a BBS FileList). You can make this datafile with a
  program called FileListMaker(from the same publisher). 

 -Select one or more Files in Dopus (from either window). Now press 
  the Button or Menu which you made in Dopus. The program starts 
  thinking and presents you with two windows on the Dopus-screen.
  One window only contains information and the other has four 
  Gadgets which you can click.

 -The four Buttons are:
  1-@{b}NOP@{ub}                - Don't do anything
  2-@{b}COPY@{ub}    -> Window  - COPY file to Assigned UTIL: dir
            -> Window  - COPY file to Assigned RENE: dir
            -> Window  - MOVE file to Assigned UTIL: dir
            -> Window  - MOVE file to Assigned RENE: dir
            -> Window  - Don't do anything
  3-@{b}DMS@{ub}     -> Window  - DMS to DF0:
            -> Window  - DMS to RAD: (Automounts RAD:) 
            -> Window  - DMS to DF1:
            -> Window  - DMS to DF2:
            -> Window  - Don't do anything
  3-@{b}LHA@{ub}     -> Window  - LHA to RAM:
            -> Window  - Don't do anything
  3-@{b}LZH@{ub}     -> Window  - LZH to RAM:
            -> Window  - Don't do anything
  3-@{b}ZIP@{ub}     -> Window  - ZIP to RAM:
            -> Window  - Don't do anything
  3-@{b}Other@{ub}   -> Window  - Read the file
            -> Window  - Execute the file
            -> Window  - Don't do anything
  4-@{b}DELETE@{ub}  -> Window  - DELETE the file
            -> Window  - NOP Don't do anything

  @{b}TO TEST@{ub}
  -Go into DOPUS

  -Goto the DIR with the File FileShow.LHA

  -Select FileShow.LHA

  -Now press your newly made Button/Menu in DOPUS

  -Wait a few seconds(go get a beer)

  -Two windows should be opening by now

  -The File.Id.diz should be in one of the windows.

  -Now You can Delete the File / Copy it / Extract it to RAM:
   or do Nothing

@endnode
